.TH "ice_sriov_configure" 9 "ice_sriov_configure" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ice_sriov_configure \- Enable or change number of VFs via sysfs
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ice_sriov_configure
.BI "(struct pci_dev *pdev "  ","
.BI "int num_vfs "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pdev" 12
pointer to a pci_dev structure
.IP "num_vfs" 12
number of VFs to allocate or 0 to free VFs
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function is called when the user updates the number of VFs in sysfs. On
success return whatever num_vfs was set to by the caller. Return negative on
failure.
